cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the development of a climbing robot and its autonomous mapping, planning, and navigation capabilities. The focus is on robotics and control (cs.RO), with a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the autonomous algorithms. Computer vision (cs.CV) is also mentioned as a sensor modality for mapping and navigation. The use of tethers and interlinked robots suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) component. Finally, the application of the climbing robot in rugged environments implies a potential connection to graphics (cs.GR) for visualization and simulation.
